"Anatomy of a Memory Piece"
After Extracting a memory piece, once your eyesight is restored, you may find two components around the device you utilized. Both should be created from your own ⁠PSYCHE Energy (Soul) if you followed the process accordingly.

The Sentience Case should be colorless at first, as it will only adapt a color after the Memory Pane has been slotted into it. These two parts can be damaged through physical or psyche means, and have the properties of stone, so caution must be taken when transporting them.

Should a Memory Piece shatter, please contact an ⁠Archkin capable of manipulating Phantasy.

Sentience Case
Initially colorless, it gets its color from the Memory Pane you slotted into it. As long as the Memory Pane's intended Sentience Category matches or is lower than the Case, you can swap cases around and it wouldn't matter.
If a Case and Panel are incompatible, the Case would retain its default pale hue.

In practice:
> Humanistic Sentience Memory Pane + Humanistic Sentience Case = ✅
> Humanistic Sentience Memory Pane + Animalistic Sentience Case = ❌
This is due to the Memory Pane being intended for Humanistic cases, it cannot be brought over to an Animalistic case as it cannot process its contents.

> Humanistic Sentience Memory Pane + Archgodic Sentience Case = ✅
> Beyonder Sentience Memory Pane + Humanistic Sentience Case = ❌
Since the 3rd example's pane is Humanistic, the Archgodic case can process the Humanistic memory pane. But for the 4th example, the Humanistic case cannot possibly fathom the contents of a Beyonder's Memory Pane. Thus, leading to incompatability.

You may notice that a discrepancy between how these cases with the issue of ⁠Thingamakin Juveniles memories not carrying over when they gain Humanistic sentience in their ⁠Thingamakin Elders stage.
This is an issue I fixed later on when inventing Memory Pieces, as I lacked foresight when creating the Thingamakin. I will admit, it is an error of mine, but I have little to no time to fix this problem.
Thingamakin can still absorb Animalistic Memory Pieces anyways, just like anyone else. There is no such thing as incompatibility between Memory Piece and the person wishing to use it.
So just extract it from them and put it back in. You can do this yourself.
> Court Note: We have been trying to fix this ourselves. But Khueen lacked sympathy towards us mortals. She could've fixed this in seconds, but refused to do so.

Memory Pane
The most important part of a Memory Piece. These are the physical manifestation of a soul's memories. By utilizing archkin conduits to vibrate the panel at a safe frequency (its original soul's natural frequency), it retains its form and color.
You may misplace the case, but never lose or break the pane.

Touching the pane may give you brief glimpses at what memories contain within, similar to when you touch someone's actual soul. This is due to the sentience in your body providing a temporary 'case' for bits of the memory to take form momentarily.
Although this was an unintended feature, I kept it in to help me categorize Memory Pieces more easily and effectively.
> Court Note: Yes, Khueen left a 'bug' in the Memory Pieces. Do with that as you will.

Capacity Cylinder
Depending on how many notches are filled in by the pane, indicates how much memories are stored within.
More details can be found in this part's dedicated section.

As for why it looks that way, I merely think the chambers of revolver guns are pretty cool. Few know this, but even if the notches fill in a clockwise manner, you can spin the chamber around to confuse others. If you have a Memory Piece, try it!
> Court Note: Yes, Khueen left an 'Easter Egg' in the Memory Pieces. Do with that as you will.

Capacity Cylinder
Found on the right side of the Memory Pane, its filled-in notches indicate how much of a soul's memory is stored within.
This is measured in a percentage-based rate.
All 8 notches filled in indicates all the memories of a soul are contained in the piece. Just 1 notch filled means less than 12.5% of a soul's memories are contained within. It may house seconds of moments or merely the base biological function skills for a person to stay alive.

Central Notch
This is the Archgodic Notch.
When filled in, this indicates that the Memory Pane belonged to an Archgod, as their memories have reached an 'ascended' form along with their ⁠Archose due to reaching Archgodhood.
> Court Note: To reiterate, All Archgodic Memory Pieces MUST be brought forward to The Vice President. Do not attempt to claim it yourself without us knowing, we will know.

Psyche Tag
This merely indicates either the general contents of a Memory Piece, or the most significant memories/experiences/skills stored within.
It glows a bright pink due to my own soul's coloration.
If the common flame is red due to it being an invention of ⁠unknown's, or electricity being a vibrant cyan following ⁠unknown's discovery of it, who am I to not make Psyche Tags' coloration follow my own.
> Court Note: Recent discoveries have indicated a rare occurrence of cyan and red Psyche Tags. Please be warry of this strange cryptic phenomena, as it may be linked to Phantasmal relations. We are still looking into it.

Baybayin writing system
You may notice the style used in all Psyche Tags follow a different orthography from both Archkin styles and those used by Mortals.
Instead, I utilized an orthography from Beyond The 4th's Wall called "Baybayin". I simply found its more elegant and mystical style flowed perfectly with that of memories, in contrast to the standard styles used by Archkin.
Plus, it seemed not many others were using it. So, I did.

If you wish to truly decipher the meaning of these tags, you must learn the writing system as well. Join me in cultural appreciation towards The Beyonds!

